    <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: hsl(150 40% 40%)">What's Actually Happening</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">Burnout is a physiological state, not a mindset problem.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <p>Chronic stress keeps your nervous system in a sustained state of activation, as your body thinks it is always managing a threat. Over time, this depletes the systems that govern energy, mood, focus, immunity, and sleep. What starts as stress becomes exhaustion, then cynicism, then a kind of functional numbness.</p>
      <p>Recovery is not about taking a week off and coming back. It is about changing the underlying relationship with stress: how you experience it, how you respond to it, and what you believe about rest, output, and your own worth.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

